Do you ever find yourself searching for a book that you >>feel<< like?

Maybe you find yourself cuddled up in your bed with a warm beverage on your nightstand and want to read a book that feels just like that. Or matches the fresh air and chirpy birds outside during spring. Or makes you feel like starting all over and getting stuff done.

Well, thats what this Club is here for.
Describe the aesthetic, the mood, the vibes you're searching for and let other people recommend you just the perfect book. The best part about a big community: Be as specific as you want! Chances are, somewhere, someone knows the right book for you.

With love,
Smoki

name: Human Book Club
description:
Inspired from the Human library organisation in Copenhagen Denmark, this club encourages speakers to share their unique life stories or fractions of them to a group of listeners. There will be no physical books instead people chatting, more like human audio book. Each speaker gets 20 mins to share their stories and a 10 mins of Q&A round where listeners or readers asks challenging questions to the book or speaker.  It will definitely be an emotional and challenging space. 

Typically, a person chooses to be a book because they believe that their story can affect another person's understanding of a certain culture, subculture, or identity.

The topics of the book of the month will vary each month so that listeners or audiences get to hear and learn about a variety of things.

Kings and kingdoms, urchins to emperors, deities and the celestial maidens, movements of religion and saints‚Äô hagiographies, love saga of cowherd and milkmaid, colossal epics and poems of poets, rivers and tales of rise and fall, anklets and rhythm of poets , of gods being human and mortals apotheosised; I always come back to literature of my soil. 

Breath and dance your love for aalta, anklets, sweet mangoes, crescent moon and everything you love about South Asian Books.

description: Yes the title for the club may be cheesy but honestly its true. Over the last 5 years I can count on one hand how many books I've read (not including textbooks). I use to read so much when I was young my parents would say I was born with a book in my hand, what happened to that girl? The answer is life. I lost my desire for reading in high school and college, life became a lot more serious and I shifted my priorities accordingly. Somewhere along the line my passion reading tapered off and I forgot how much I truly loved it. That is why I am creating this club, you have all expressed your interest in joining a book club but say you have no time or cant commit to reading. Well, consider us your new accountability partners. I want everyone to rekindle their love and passion for literature and share that with all of us. Welcome to Busy Bee's Book Club!

how the club works:
¬∑ every month, there will be one book to read which will be decided by the members themselves!
¬∑ at the end of the month, there will be a discussion and prompt questions for members to share their insights about the book and its antiheroes
